WEBVTT

04:48.770 --> 04:49.871
Thank you, Taylor.

04:51.593 --> 04:52.394
Merry Christmas.

04:53.795 --> 04:54.616
Merry Christmas.

05:00.702 --> 05:04.206
It's the best season I like it.

05:04.226 --> 05:04.866
Do you love it?

05:05.667 --> 05:14.856
I know you have some of the men who would like to do some last-minute shopping.

05:14.996 --> 05:16.658
We still have four days.

05:18.274 --> 05:23.341
And some of you have some business to do.

05:24.082 --> 05:28.548
I promise you, I let you out before two o'clock.

05:29.970 --> 05:30.992
Are we okay with that?

05:32.354 --> 05:32.674
No.

05:32.694 --> 05:42.928
Today, I want to speak about love.

05:44.831 --> 05:47.154
Everybody likes the subject of love.

05:48.034 --> 05:49.356
And Mike started it.

05:50.017 --> 05:51.599
I said, here goes my message.

05:52.260 --> 05:57.146
But Mike is not a thief like Dean and Ken.

05:59.409 --> 06:06.378
And thank God it was a blessing to me what he said.

06:07.400 --> 06:12.106
And today I want to tell you about the love story.

06:14.750 --> 06:18.034
I want to read a small verse.

06:19.234 --> 06:30.250
And this verse says, in John went 14, and the Word became flesh and dwelt amongst us.

06:32.553 --> 06:34.656
The Word became flesh.

06:35.858 --> 06:42.487
The Word is Jesus, is God, and dwelt He came down amongst us.

06:44.009 --> 06:44.530
Let's pray.

06:46.530 --> 06:48.012
We thank you for your word.

06:48.072 --> 06:50.936
We thank you for that beautiful song.

06:51.036 --> 06:53.099
We thank you for the breaking of bread.

06:53.179 --> 06:59.608
We thank you for every person who's in attendance here and those who are not here.

07:00.970 --> 07:02.291
Lord, we are thankful.

07:03.333 --> 07:04.675
We are so thankful.

07:05.736 --> 07:13.026
So bless us with your voice, not mine, and your word, not anyone's word.

07:13.627 --> 07:15.389
In Jesus' name we pray.

07:15.409 --> 07:15.890
Amen.

07:17.378 --> 07:27.689
Long time ago in Bethlehem, a baby came into our world to bring peace to all nations.

07:29.331 --> 07:35.037
What a change is coming, road to us.

07:37.239 --> 07:47.090
One of the astute Irish historians and essayists once wrote

07:49.154 --> 08:05.190
The three short years of the public ministry of Jesus have done more to soften and regenerate humankind than all the moralizing.

08:05.771 --> 08:08.053
Bear with me, I hope I can spell it right.

08:08.594 --> 08:16.402
All the moralizing of all the moralists and all the philosophizing

08:18.242 --> 08:22.467
of all the philosophers since the word began.

08:22.487 --> 08:28.994
I have two words for you.

08:29.614 --> 08:38.684
God, God's love is manifested in His plan for you and for me.

08:40.646 --> 08:48.114
God has a plan for you, but God, He has manifested this, and I want to use

08:48.194 --> 08:56.586
John 3.16 to begin with, for God so loved the world that He gave His only Son.

08:58.648 --> 09:03.675
And through His Son Jesus, He won the world.

09:05.558 --> 09:06.479
Do you agree with that?

09:06.920 --> 09:07.881
He won the world.

09:09.664 --> 09:17.074
The Bible says in Ephesians 5.27 that He, God Christ, might

09:17.794 --> 09:25.285
present to himself the church in all her glory, having no spot, no wrinkle.

09:25.646 --> 09:27.308
This is the church of God.

09:27.949 --> 09:31.654
That's what he wants it to be, no spot.

09:33.677 --> 09:45.074
In all her glory, no wrinkle or any such thing, but that she should be the holy blameless church.

09:47.298 --> 09:49.180
I'm talking about you, not the building.

09:50.961 --> 09:56.507
What a plan God had for his people.

09:57.848 --> 10:07.477
It's a plan available to all children, a plan that involves past, present, and future.

10:08.758 --> 10:10.580
His redemption passed.

10:12.082 --> 10:16.786
Everyone who is redeemed, you have been redeemed in the past.

10:16.866 --> 10:17.346
Amen?

10:18.608 --> 10:25.655
His sanctification for now and His glorification for the future.

10:26.175 --> 10:27.056
That's the plan.

10:28.297 --> 10:29.499
That's God's plan.

10:30.059 --> 10:31.961
What a loving Savior.

10:32.642 --> 10:36.686
Remember, I want to talk about His love today.

10:37.847 --> 10:39.669
And what a love story.

10:40.730 --> 10:42.772
You know, God is love.

10:44.033 --> 10:45.074
God is love.

10:48.322 --> 10:50.565
And you know why you ask, why do you love me?

10:51.046 --> 10:53.410
Because he can answer, because I am love.

10:54.872 --> 10:56.535
I can't give anything but love.

10:57.576 --> 10:58.738
And that's our God.

11:00.621 --> 11:01.542
Enjoy his love.

11:02.223 --> 11:04.126
We're basking in his love.

11:06.129 --> 11:10.917
God has loved us in the past, I said, now and in the future.

11:12.059 --> 11:14.322
And God, God's love.

11:16.354 --> 11:25.046
for us is not determined by our attractiveness, nor performance.

11:27.049 --> 11:29.532
Oh, you deserve, Alan deserves my love.

11:29.592 --> 11:30.594
I'll give him my love.

11:31.535 --> 11:31.735
No.

11:33.418 --> 11:35.160
Taylor deserves my love.

11:35.240 --> 11:36.702
No, it's not.

11:37.503 --> 11:39.146
That's an attractive person.

11:41.349 --> 11:41.889
I love him.

11:42.190 --> 11:43.291
This is not Jesus.

11:44.613 --> 11:45.234
Jesus.

11:46.018 --> 11:47.239
Doesn't look at that.

11:47.700 --> 11:51.964
He looks at you as a person he loves.

11:54.206 --> 11:56.008
And he says, I came.

11:57.589 --> 12:02.334
I came born in a manger because I love you.

12:08.040 --> 12:14.226
And God's love is, as we say in our all-inclusive

12:15.906 --> 12:17.028
all inclusive.

12:18.530 --> 12:25.140
There's a children chorus I learned long time ago when I was a little guy.

12:25.881 --> 12:36.036
And it says, red and yellow, black and white, all are precious in his solid.

12:38.039 --> 12:45.010
No person is so high or so low that he or she is not

12:45.282 --> 12:47.024
the object of his love.

12:51.330 --> 12:54.415
Jesus loves you and loves me.

12:57.078 --> 13:14.482
As we celebrate the birth of Jesus in about four days, and as we rush to friends, families, and all to get together, I tell you one thing.

13:14.722 --> 13:15.543
This is good.

13:16.263 --> 13:17.365
This is beautiful.

13:17.945 --> 13:21.809
But let us ask ourselves these questions.

13:22.790 --> 13:30.077
Are we prepared to show in our lives a true picture of his love?

13:33.320 --> 13:33.620
Are we?

13:37.464 --> 13:39.826
Does he see a deep, true love for him?

13:39.866 --> 13:43.730
Or he sees just seasonal affection?

13:45.410 --> 13:46.872
Seasonal affection.

13:47.773 --> 13:52.318
When Christmas is over, all everything is gone.

13:53.019 --> 14:01.830
Bring the lives down and everything, and we forget about it and go our way and live our life the way we know it.

14:04.633 --> 14:06.335
Is it a matter of affection?

14:10.280 --> 14:12.082
Some emotional thing

14:15.202 --> 14:16.924
Is it a holiday to have fun?

14:18.686 --> 14:28.378
Are we serious about carrying the good news, the good news of his coming to people we meet on a daily basis?

14:30.380 --> 14:42.354
Have a message carried by the angel says, behold, I bring you good news of a great joy, which shall be for all people.

14:43.522 --> 14:52.791
Do we recognize that we should be the carriers of this heavenly message?

14:57.256 --> 15:02.101
Do we recognize Christ on Christmas?

15:05.524 --> 15:11.250
Do we really understand the purpose of His coming

15:14.338 --> 15:30.975
Not long ago, a professor of psychology in one of our great universities gave a word suggestion test, and all that class did take the test.

15:30.995 --> 15:41.586
Now it says, right after the word Christmas, the first thought that flashes through your mind regarding that day.

15:43.810 --> 15:47.253
There were about 40 students there.

15:47.273 --> 15:56.222
These were the answers.

15:56.242 --> 15:56.502
Three.

15:59.825 --> 16:01.187
He gave them the word Christmas.

16:02.328 --> 16:03.829
Some of them says, three.

16:04.870 --> 16:07.152
Another answer, holly.

16:08.814 --> 16:10.415
Another one, mistletoe.

16:12.317 --> 16:13.138
Presence.

16:14.146 --> 16:26.145
Turkey, holiday, carols, and Santa Claus, but no one had written, birthday of Jesus.

16:31.133 --> 16:37.824
As we celebrate, is he forgotten and are we sinking in the celebrations?

16:39.987 --> 16:41.810
Did we forget about his love?

16:47.490 --> 17:01.068
As I believe, as there were no room for him in the end, there is no room for him today in the celebration of Christmas.

17:07.477 --> 17:09.179
We forgot why he came.

17:16.489 --> 17:17.010
Another

17:17.378 --> 17:18.819
thing I want to bring to you.

17:18.939 --> 17:24.365
God's love is manifested in his sacrifice on the cross.

17:26.006 --> 17:33.113
Let's face it, ceremonial festivals, dazzling decorations.

17:33.213 --> 17:35.055
I like to go and watch them.

17:35.635 --> 17:40.880
And I drive with Shelley at night and say, oh, our neighborhood is really lighting up.

17:41.341 --> 17:41.681
Yeah.

17:43.463 --> 17:47.026
Super artistic performance, have you watched some

17:47.426 --> 17:53.474
some of their TV presentation about Christmas.

17:55.316 --> 18:03.747
These things are good to celebrate, but they do not leave a lasting impression.

18:05.229 --> 18:07.812
It's passing.

18:07.832 --> 18:11.017
Come Thursday, come Friday, it's no more.

18:12.699 --> 18:15.282
What lasts is the love of Jesus.

18:18.114 --> 18:32.853
This word can only be reached and touched by Christ of the simple gospel, by Christ's love toward each and every person.

18:34.035 --> 18:37.219
He is a Savior for all the people.

18:37.299 --> 18:42.185
That's the message of heaven that was transmitted by the angel.

18:44.829 --> 18:45.650
And we should do it.

18:47.682 --> 18:48.704
We should do it.

18:50.026 --> 19:05.231
If we truly love Him, if we truly honor His presence, if we truly honor His condescension, that means His coming, we should preach the love of God.

19:05.611 --> 19:10.780
We should witness this about the story of love.

19:10.800 --> 19:14.706
God loves us that He sent Jesus

19:18.754 --> 19:32.893
And you know, if we engage in telling the world about this love story, we shall reach every continent like the disciples of old.

19:32.913 --> 19:38.761
They have turned the world upside down with love through love.

19:39.021 --> 19:40.964
Simple Jesus loves you.

19:43.127 --> 19:46.071
Jesus loves you.

19:46.091 --> 19:48.594
Question, are we celebrating?

19:50.626 --> 19:59.420
Jesus' love and his redemption, or we are blinded by the festivities for getting the meaning of Christmas.

20:05.710 --> 20:13.422
I pray that this simple message I repeated, he became flesh and dwelt amongst us.

20:16.767 --> 20:18.610
He lived for

20:19.010 --> 20:30.666
about 33 years and hear people when they put their name Christmas, Holly Jolly, right?

20:30.966 --> 20:32.568
That's what they remembered.

20:32.909 --> 20:40.319
The students, 40 students, none of them mentioned Jesus Christ.

20:47.128 --> 20:48.370
A God in man said,

20:50.146 --> 20:52.749
Sin is man's tragedy.

20:53.810 --> 20:54.891
That's why God came.

20:55.592 --> 20:57.334
And Jesus is God's answer.

21:06.363 --> 21:07.925
We should make it a challenge.

21:10.708 --> 21:20.018
This season and throughout the year, during what's left to celebrate

21:20.226 --> 21:20.747
Christmas.

21:21.167 --> 21:22.689
This should be our challenge.

21:25.533 --> 21:26.954
God loves you.

21:29.097 --> 21:31.180
Can you preach this word?

21:31.200 --> 21:32.742
Can anyone say this word?

21:33.443 --> 21:34.324
God loves you.

21:36.907 --> 21:38.068
You can open with this.

21:42.254 --> 21:48.882
Let's not resign ourselves to the festivities, shopping,

21:50.562 --> 22:00.932
God bless, giving and receiving gifts, family gathering together, decorating the Christmas tree and decorating outside.

22:01.332 --> 22:02.213
They're all good.

22:03.834 --> 22:10.781
My house has all the, you know, lights I could have.

22:12.783 --> 22:15.946
And we have, I love the Christmas tree.

22:16.286 --> 22:19.209
I love to light it, turn it off at night.

22:19.609 --> 22:20.370
Shelly does it.

22:21.058 --> 22:25.985
So I love that, but Christianity is a higher calling.

22:28.469 --> 22:29.130
That is good.

22:29.791 --> 22:31.674
Christianity is a higher calling.

22:33.116 --> 22:43.692
Let us go out and present our Christian life, our Christian beliefs, Christianity, the way it should be presented to the world.

22:45.915 --> 22:46.836
That's the challenge.

22:48.539 --> 22:50.802
That's how we should celebrate Christmas.

22:51.330 --> 22:51.991
enjoying.

22:52.431 --> 22:56.636
And do you have the Lord Jesus in your heart?

22:56.656 --> 23:11.613
Christmas is taking His coming, believing in Him and taking Him as your own Savior, as your own person who came to love you and die for you and die for me.

23:12.434 --> 23:15.618
This is when you celebrate Christmas.

23:15.798 --> 23:19.442
And if you're not a believer yet,

23:20.674 --> 23:25.762
May I ask you to take the Lord Jesus into your heart?

23:26.383 --> 23:30.490
Said, Lord, you came and died for me.

23:30.530 --> 23:41.227
Allow me to open my heart and have Jesus live in there during this Christmas season.

23:41.367 --> 23:48.178
And when you live like this, and you'll never forget it because you got saved on Christmas.

23:48.930 --> 23:53.035
every Christmas that I invite you to do that.

23:53.055 --> 23:59.963
I invite you to come to Jesus, Lord, Lord, enter my heart.

23:59.983 --> 24:06.150
Let's not forget the primary reason for this coming.

24:06.170 --> 24:11.136
And let's remember this is the story of love.

24:12.878 --> 24:16.082
We need to honor Him.

24:18.210 --> 24:27.058
And the church is, is there any chance before Christmas comes to do something special for the Lord?

24:28.159 --> 24:35.907
Ask yourself this, can I go out and witness what Jesus did in my life?

24:40.611 --> 24:47.858
Or only we're waiting for the celebration for Christmas Eve to open the gifts, allow me

24:48.930 --> 24:51.233
or Christmas Day morning?

24:54.096 --> 24:55.819
Are we looking at that excitement?

24:57.260 --> 24:59.063
Or, which is good?

24:59.703 --> 25:00.845
I'm not condemning it.

25:01.726 --> 25:02.467
I have the same.

25:03.108 --> 25:06.972
But can we go a little bit beyond the 25th?

25:13.080 --> 25:14.061
Can we do something?

25:14.782 --> 25:18.066
I think we have still the chance to do it.

25:20.738 --> 25:25.903
I mentioned about two, three weeks ago, Cynthia had a book with stories.

25:27.545 --> 25:29.827
And I have access to it now.

25:34.952 --> 25:48.466
And I read a beautiful story, actual story, about a young lady who wanted to do something

25:48.898 --> 25:50.801
for Jesus on Christmas.

25:51.783 --> 25:52.884
And here's the story.

25:54.086 --> 26:03.221
Julianne Holland, her name, age 13, wanted to do something special for Jesus at Christmas.

26:04.323 --> 26:08.690
She addressed her letter about Jesus to the local post office.

26:10.412 --> 26:14.439
It went to the desk of Donald L. Orner.

26:15.520 --> 26:16.562
You can check that out.

26:16.962 --> 26:24.389
Director of the Customer Services at the Postal Center in Harrisburg, Pennsylvania.

26:25.350 --> 26:28.153
Julianne's letter, he opened it and read it.

26:29.434 --> 26:39.864
Every Christmas people think about getting presents, getting together with friends, and having a good time because Jesus was war.

26:39.884 --> 26:40.985
No.

26:41.005 --> 26:45.650
By being born, he let love into the world, let blind

26:46.658 --> 26:51.103
People see, 13 years old, let the crippled people walk.

26:52.184 --> 27:04.478
So for this Christmas, don't think about your presence, just think about Jesus and all he did and try to spread the real spirit of Christmas.

27:05.539 --> 27:07.441
She signed it and made it.

27:08.882 --> 27:15.730
Omer, the Director of the Customer Service at the Post Office,

27:15.970 --> 27:23.642
replied to the letter saying, my dear Julian, we have no mail route to heaven.

27:26.005 --> 27:29.691
But I'm sure that Jesus is aware of what you wrote.

27:31.333 --> 27:45.074
He knows our thoughts and our feelings, and your beautiful letter flowed out across all the miles that no mailman could ever travel and touch

27:45.538 --> 27:46.279
his heart.

27:49.224 --> 28:01.243
Perhaps too, Julian, some of those who ask for presence are really asking for love, but to know that they are loved, they need some physical object to show it.

28:02.565 --> 28:09.776
You said that your letter wouldn't get anywhere, but it touched my heart, Merry Christmas, and may God bless you.

28:11.820 --> 28:13.362
The Associated Press

28:15.106 --> 28:19.433
Relay Julian's beautiful letter around the world.

28:22.257 --> 28:26.885
There was Angela Stimes featured it on the front page.

28:28.768 --> 28:39.004
And that's how Julian touched the world.

28:39.024 --> 28:40.306
It's the love of God.

28:45.634 --> 28:51.500
Shall we reciprocate his love a little bit during this Christmas season?

28:54.202 --> 28:55.684
A little bit of his love.

28:56.204 --> 29:00.288
We can never match it and do something for him.

29:05.493 --> 29:14.802
Show some compassion, spread his love until the world, the purpose.

29:15.298 --> 29:16.059
of his coming.

29:18.383 --> 29:23.691
God bless you and have a wonderful Christmas season.

29:25.213 --> 29:25.634
I'm done.

29:25.654 --> 29:35.689
And you're not going to stay till 2 p.m. And I wish you all a very Merry Christmas and a joyous one.

29:35.869 --> 29:37.472
Let's bow heads for brothers.

29:40.677 --> 29:44.242
Thank you, Father, for sending

29:44.418 --> 29:51.389
you'll only be loved son to die on the cross to save us from sin.

29:51.409 --> 29:52.170
Set us free.

29:53.231 --> 29:55.335
What kind of love is this?

29:57.999 --> 30:01.724
It's greater far, as the song says, than anything.

30:01.785 --> 30:07.914
And we cannot write about it, sing about it, describe it, witness.

30:07.974 --> 30:09.236
We cannot do enough.

30:12.060 --> 30:13.202
You love the world.

30:13.474 --> 30:14.836
He still loves the world.

30:15.376 --> 30:21.163
You love us and you will still love us because God is love.

30:22.284 --> 30:25.628
And the Bible says, thank you for that.

30:26.609 --> 30:28.471
He loves till the end.

30:29.832 --> 30:31.634
There is no ending to your love.

30:32.636 --> 30:37.441
We thank you during this Christmas season to show this love.

30:38.402 --> 30:41.906
We still have some time to show this love and live

30:42.370 --> 30:50.020
to honor his name and praise his holy name amongst us.

30:51.702 --> 30:54.425
Bless each and everyone and dismiss us.

30:55.467 --> 31:00.874
We pray in his wonderful name, Jesus Christ, for our Savior.

31:02.376 --> 31:02.616
Amen.

31:02.916 --> 31:03.998
The meeting is over.

31:04.538 --> 31:07.442
Thank you for listening to me and may God bless you.

